The Lagos State Commissioner of Police, CP Sylvester Abiodun Alabi, has commissioned six blocks of offices of Ijaiye Ojokoro Police Station along Agbado Ijaiye Road on Wednesday, April 13, 2022. The new blocks were built by the Divisional Police Officer (DPO) of the station, Chief Superintendent of Police, CSP Ogunsakin Gbenga, and his men. Ogunsakin who assumed at the station less than two years ago said the office blocks were meant to give more offices to police officers to perform their administrative duties. In his own speech, Lagos State Commissioner for Police, CP Sylvester Abiodun Alabi, lauded the bold step of the DPO and his team for providing more offices for Police officers to perform their daily duties. The commissioner said the renovation of other stations were ongoing in all police formations across the country by the Police authorities. Ogunsakin also assured he commissioner that other buildings inside the Police Station would be completed in due course, this according to DPO, are church and mosque being undertaken by the Christian and Muslim communities in the area. Meanwhile, the chairman of Ojokoro Local Council Development Area in Lagos State, Hon. Hameed Idowu Tijani (alias HID), has also donated a Toyota car to the Ijaiye Ojokoro Police Station to reduce their transportation problem and to facilitate their movements during the official assignments.